 HN1[
] City Municipal Code section 33.3917 reads: "No charge in excess of Two Dollars and Fifty Cents ($ 2.50) per hour 
shall be collected from any player for the privilege of participating in any game."

 HN3[
] The Cartwright Act, in Business and Professions Code section 16702, defines "persons" to include "corporations, firms, partnerships and associations existing under or authorized by the laws of this State or any other State, or any foreign 
country."

